OL,3,CHeatwave declared in Jersey as islands
OL,4,Cswelter in record temperatures
OL,6,FJersey is officially in a heatwave as
OL,7,Fthe Channel Islands swelter under
OL,8,Fcontinued record-breaking temperatures.
OL,10,FSensors at the Maison St Louis
OL,11,FObservatory in St Saviour already
OL,12,Frecorded 28 degrees Celsius on Tuesday
OL,13,Fmorning (26 May), marking three
OL,14,Fconsecutive days when the maximum air
OL,15,Ftemperature has exceeded the level to
OL,16,Fdeclare a heatwave.
OL,18,FJersey recorded its hottest May day
OL,19,Fever on Monday with the mercury
OL,20,Fpeaking at 31.9 degrees, breaking the
OL,21,Frecord of 30.1 degrees from Sunday.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/6
