PN,38102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F381A1779876311
OL,3,CHeatwave declared in Jersey as islands
OL,4,Cswelter in record temperatures
OL,6,FTemperatures are expected to peak on
OL,7,FTuesday afternoon and to stay above
OL,8,Faverage for the rest of the week.
OL,10,FMeanwhile, Guernsey is expected to
OL,11,Freach the official heatwave marker on
OL,12,FWednesday before gradually easing off
OL,13,Finto the weekend and next week.
OL,15,FThe island also recorded its hottest
OL,16,Fever May day as temperatures climbed
OL,17,Fto 30.8 degrees at Guernsey Airport on
OL,18,FMonday, and could creep up further on
OL,19,FTuesday.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/6
